How to Style Ethnic Wear from BIBA?
After buying the clothes one thing, styling them is the most important part of enhancing the entire look. If you are confused about styling your ethnic wear, don’t worry we have got you covered. Here are some of the styling tips for your traditional day wear:

Go for bright-colored kurta sets or Anarkali if you want a festive look. You can style them with a matching heavy dupatta. Choose a contrasting color dupatta to create a more edgy look. If you are wearing a blue kurta set, team it up with a hot pink dupatta. Trust me I would look super good.
If you are looking for a more sober look, choose a pastel shade of Anarkali (brownie points if it's white). Pair this up with a bright-colored dupatta and matching big chandbali earrings. To accessorise, pair it with a mojari and not a sandal this time. Mojaris look extraordinarily trendy and suit ethnic wear the most.
Glam it up with makeup! Good makeup can lift the look instantly. You can go for a vibrant eyeshadow or dark-colored lipstick to accentuate the look. Just make sure to highlight just one part of your face. If you are doing heavy eye makeup, go lighter on the lips and vice versa.
Carry a nice bag to elevate the look. Go for a mirror work bag or an embroidered potli bag to carry as an accessory.

Dressing sensibly simply means being conscious of how you look, knowing what clothes suit you, and learning how to present oneself as appealing. It also shows your character and way of life. Always choose ethnic wear that suits your personality and style. BIBA ethnic collection has something for each type of fashion lover. No matter if you love to dress up sober or glam, you will find something in the BIBA online dress collection.
